The paper focuses on Cloud-based Mobile Augmentation (CMA) approaches, which involve utilizing cloud resources to enhance the computing capabilities of mobile devices. This topic falls under the mobile computing domain, which is covered by the cs.MOBILE sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cloud resources, which is relevant to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also discusses decision making and performance limitations, which are relevant to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of CMA approaches on mobile computing and presents open challenges, which are relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
